  "description": [
    "heINDI AMLEADER1 A WEEKLY PUBLICATION DEVOTED TO INDIANSAND INDIAN EDUCATION ISSUED EVERY FRIDAY DURING THE SCHOOL YEAR BY HASKELL INSTITUTE Aan Slepol III Muaumun mere MI 2 VOL XXXVI LAWRENCE KANS OCTOBER 21 1932 NO 8 MEDICINE LODGE CELEBRATES TREATY ANNIVERSARY Sixtyfive years ago this month a peace treaty was signed in Medicine Lodge Kans between the five plains tribes of Indians in the State and the Federal Government The incident was directly responsible for ending a bloody war that had been in progress between the plains Indians and the white race for three years one that promised to go on indefinitely It also made possible the settement of all western Kansas Colorado the two Dakotas New Mexico and Arizona Medicine Lodge observed the anniversary October 5 6 and 7 with a historical pageant which faithfully portrayed the event which also made possible the completion of the Union Pacific Railroad and cleared the way for the building of the Santa Fe a few years later substituting the railroad for the old Santa Fe trail A GIGANTIC PAGEANT The celebration took the form of a gigantic pageant and was presented in a natural amphitheater which was the scene of the peace"
  ],
